description: Internal and external alterations including the removal of structural elements and fabric involving the partial demolition of timber floors and ceiling, removal and replacement of timber joists, removal of timber beams, insertion of steel beams to form a concrete deck at ground floor level, and removal of window frames and glazing (Listed Building Consent)
decision_conditions: The development permitted shall be begun before the expiration of three years from the date of this permission.
Reason:  In order to comply with the provisions of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended).

| The development hereby approved shall be carried out in accordance with drawing numbers Cover Letter ref. PD10949/CM/GK/KFH, dated 10 February 2017, prepared by Montagu Evans; Site Location Plan scale 1:2500; Twyford Abbey: Stage 1 preliminary timber condition investigation of the main house - south wing, site note 9 for 9 and 10 November 2016, job. No 146.24, by Hutton + Rostron Environmental Investigations Limited; Twyford Abbey: Stage 1 preliminary timber condition investigation of the main house - east wing, Site note 8 for 9 and 10 November 2016, job No. 146.24, by Hutton + Rostron Environmental Investigations Limited; Twyford Abbey: Stage 1 preliminary condition investigation of the exteriors of the main house, Site note 1 for 9 and 10 October 0216, job No. 146.24, by Hutton + Rostron Environmental Investigations Limited; Preliminary Structural Inspection Report, ref. 25741 version 3, dated February 2017, by Price & Myers; Method Statement - Initial Emergency Enabling Works Twyford Abbey, Twyford Abbey Park Royal NW10 7DE; Basement Plan, ref. 25741 page E1; Ground Floor Plan, ref. 25741 page E2 rev 2; First Floor Plan, ref. 25741 page E3 rev 2; Second Floor Plan, ref. 25741 page E4; Ground Floor Plan, ref. 25741 page SK-R1 rev 2; First Floor Plan, ref. 25741 page SK-R2 rev 2; Second Floor Plan, ref. 25741 page SK-R3 rev 2; Outline Sequence for Removal of Floors, ref. 25741 page SK-R4 rev 2; Proposed Access Deck to Room G17/F24-F25-F26, ref. 25741 page SK-R5; North - Chapel Wing Ground Floor, ref. 25741 page SK-CWG, dated 17 March 2017 and received 24 March 2017; Proposed Floor Rooms G1 & G2, Ground Floor Plan, ref. 25741 page SK-FGa, dated 24 February 2017 and received 24 March 2017; Ground Floor, ref. 25741 page SK-GK, dated 17 March 2017 and received 24 March 2017; North Wing of Courtyard - Proposed, ref. 25741 page SK-HCGI rev A, dated 1 March 2017 and received 24 March 2017; Written Scheme of Investigation for Clearance and Removal of Damaged Parts at Twyford Abbey for 29 March 2017, Job No. 146.24, by Hutton + Rostron Environmental Investigations Limited, received 7 April 2017.

Reason:  For the avoidance of doubt and in the interest of proper planning, in accordance with Policies 1.1, 1.2 and 3.8 of the Ealing Core Strategy (2012); policies 7.4 and 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013); policies 7.4 and 7.6 of the London Plan (2016); and the National Planning Policy Framework (2012).

| No demolition or development shall take place other than in accordance with the agreed Written Scheme of Investigation for Historic Building Recording during the clearance and removal of damaged parts at Twyford Abbey (Hutton+Rustron, 2017).  In accordance with the agreed Written Scheme of Investigation, the condition will not be satisfied until the historic building recording for this phase of development has been completed and a written record of the results has been submitted to and approved by the local planning authority in writing and in consultation with Historic England.

Reason: To establish the character, history, dating, form and development of the historic building or structure in accordance with policy 7C of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013); policies 1.1(h) and 1.2 (g) of the Ealing Development (Core) Strategy (2012); and policy 7.8 of the London Plan (2016).

| Following removal of the timber floor structure at ground floor level, further details and a methodology are to be agreed through meetings/discussion and confirmed in writing with Historic England and the Local Planning Authority as to the installation of the concrete floor structure and associated interventions to historic masonry.

Reason:  To safeguard the significance of the listed building by limiting harm to its fabric in accordance with policy 7C of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013); policies 1.1(h) and 1.2 (g) of the Ealing Development (Core) Strategy (2012); and policy 7.8 of the London Plan (2016).

| Prior to removal of any primary beams at first and second floor levels, further details and a methodology are to be agreed through a meeting with Historic England regarding safeguarding the structural stability of the building, including guarding against induced movement at beam supports, and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority.

Reason:  To safeguard the significance of the listed building by limiting harm to its fabric in accordance with policy 7C of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013); policies 1.1(h) and 1.2 (g) of the Ealing Development (Core) Strategy (2012); and policy 7.8 of the London Plan (2016).
